          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-05-19 15:06:21" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>a state of severe distress, aroused by intense concern for impending pain, danger, evil, etc., or possibly by the illusion of such circumstances</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>fear</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In a number of languages there is no noun-like word for ‘fear.’ Accordingly, expressions containing such a noun in Greek must often be restructured so that the corresponding semantic unit may be expressed by a verb. Therefore, instead of ‘fear,’ one may have expressions such as ‘be afraid’ or ‘to fear.’ Instead of ‘fears within’ ({S:04700700500040}), one may translate ‘in our hearts we were afraid.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
